rComments: Her tests are super, super fair, and her lectures are organized and easy to follow/understand. If she didn't know the answer to a question, she would actually research it and answer next class. She made sure everyone knew what was going on assignment wise. There are weekly assignments but they're 6 multiple choice questions and super easy.

Erin is great. She has very organized teaching style and lecture presentations.  She provides clear feedback on tests and assignments and looks for and sends articles to those who have additional curiosities.  She organizes her lectures and tests in a manner that doesn't require extensive reading and note taking from the book.
